parameters.description: Log of COTS intrinsic growth rate (year^-1). Corresponds to r_cots = 2.0, representing potential for population doubling annually during favorable conditions.
Log of COTS carrying capacity (individuals/m2). Corresponds to K_cots = 2.0, representing maximum sustainable density during outbreak conditions.
Log of COTS natural mortality rate (year^-1). Corresponds to m_cots = 0.5, representing 50% annual mortality in absence of starvation.
Log of fast-growing coral intrinsic growth rate (year^-1). Corresponds to r_fast = 1.5, representing 150% potential annual increase for Acropora species.
Log of fast-growing coral carrying capacity (%). Corresponds to K_fast = 50%, representing maximum sustainable cover for Acropora species.
Log of slow-growing coral intrinsic growth rate (year^-1). Corresponds to r_slow = 0.5, representing 50% potential annual increase for Faviidae and Porites species.
Log of slow-growing coral carrying capacity (%). Corresponds to K_slow = 30%, representing maximum sustainable cover for Faviidae and Porites species.
Log of COTS attack rate on fast-growing coral (m2/individual/year). Corresponds to a_fast = 0.1, representing area of fast coral consumed per COTS annually.
Log of COTS attack rate on slow-growing coral (m2/individual/year). Corresponds to a_slow = 0.05, representing area of slow coral consumed per COTS annually.
Log of handling time for fast-growing coral (year/%). Corresponds to h_fast = 0.01, representing time spent handling per unit of fast coral.
Log of handling time for slow-growing coral (year/%). Corresponds to h_slow = 0.02, representing time spent handling per unit of slow coral.
Log of preference factor for fast-growing coral (dimensionless). Corresponds to pref = 2.0, indicating COTS prefer fast-growing coral twice as much as slow-growing coral.
Log of optimal temperature for COTS reproduction (°C). Corresponds to temp_opt = 28°C, the temperature at which COTS reproduction is maximized.
Log of temperature response width (°C). Corresponds to temp_width = 2°C, representing the width of the temperature response curve.
Log of coral threshold for COTS reproduction (%). Corresponds to coral_threshold = 10%, representing minimum coral cover needed for successful COTS reproduction.
Log of steepness of coral limitation function (dimensionless). Corresponds to coral_steepness = 1.0, controlling how sharply COTS reproduction responds to coral availability.
Log of observation error SD for COTS. Corresponds to obs_sd_cots = 0.2, representing 20% observation error in COTS abundance.
Log of observation error SD for fast-growing coral. Corresponds to obs_sd_fast = 0.3, representing 30% observation error in fast coral cover.
Log of observation error SD for slow-growing coral. Corresponds to obs_sd_slow = 0.3, representing 30% observation error in slow coral cover.
Log of process error SD for COTS. Corresponds to proc_sd_cots = 0.3, representing 30% process error in COTS population dynamics.
Log of process error SD for fast-growing coral. Corresponds to proc_sd_fast = 0.2, representing 20% process error in fast coral dynamics.
Log of process error SD for slow-growing coral. Corresponds to proc_sd_slow = 0.2, representing 20% process error in slow coral dynamics.
